	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Johannesburg – A man was killed when his vehicle rolled multiple times off the Golden Highway in Vanderbijlpark, paramedics said on Sunday. ER24 spokesperson Russel Meiring said paramedics arrived on the scene to find the vehicle on the side of the road, lying on its roof. "The body of the man was found lying quite a distance away from his vehicle. Paramedics assessed the man and found that he had sustained numerous injuries and showed no signs of life. Unfortunately, nothing could be done for him and he was declared dead." He said it was unclear how the crash occurred but said police were on scene to investigate. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  